column5: First,  Sorry DouG and Fidel (we've tried the phone/fish thing, I suck) and everybody who has had awesome reports. I meant to reply to your reports awhile back but for reasons below, I could not.  Reasons for OFC absence. 1. No home computer 2. No office computer access 3. Life   I had some time off so I jumped in to share this moment.  I haven't been out fishing as much as I would like!!!!  This is the first Walleye I've caught down here. I had no intention of catching anything. I was trying to even out my farmers tan for a few minutes and was using a telescopic rod that was left in the van. I went to deep water and casted in a worm. I was most alarmed at what transpired next.    I haven't caught an "eye" this big anywhere in Ontario.  Now I know how Cliff and Carol feel. sort of. Since CCMT, BLY, the Urban Fisherman and Jon (fishing fury) have caught them nearby. I figured it was only a matter of time.  I'll be contacting Misfish for some weightloss tips  See you later,  S.  PS. I might be a little slow to reply!!   EDIT: Original image was to blurred even for me so I cropped it. Mu tummy still remains

lol AWESOME DUDE!  Congrats.  Thanks for the shout-out, although I never did repeat my success before moving away from the big smoke.  ...and once you're able to consult with Misfish hook me up - I've put on a solid 25lbs in the last year even if it doesn't look like it.  Nice to hear from you.  Cheers
Grant, I read the title of your post and laughed out loud.  Congratulations!  Try to stay in touch, eh?  Jeeeze.

Nice work man.. and thank you for blurring out everything. Now people will not only never find your spot, but they won't be crowding you for tips when they see you down there. Good strategy!  But really, congrats. That's a beast.

Yeah, the winter fat has lingered. Good thing I'm married and it doesn't matter how I look!   For reasons we discussed whilst fishing before, I'm swamped! I hope you sang out loud too! Fall's looking better?????   Thanks Rich, I should also consult with you on the weightloss thing.  You nailed it though. I give tips freely but enjoy my privacy these days. (I don't want the OFC wives using my image as a screensaver either)  cheers!
The elusive Snag lives!!  Was begiining to think you had been pantywhupped or locked up for life (it happens).  Nice walleye, Certainly miss reading your most entertaining reports.

HAHAAH!!  That's funny G.  I only seem to get the calls when you catch something.  "Oh yeah I was gonna tell you...downtown..YESTERDAY..!!"  "Dude, you woudln't believe it...I got my first walleye.. YESTERDAY..!!"  You must use a pretty big spatula to be able to spread it on that thick...  That's an awesome fish budday.  Nice Molson muscle too heheheh  HD

Thanks Big, BTW I am pantywhupped.   Not fair,  What about the "in the moment" calls where I tie-up your inbox with my girlish fish panic?   Hey, Don't be insensitive, I just gave birth to twins a week ago.
Grant your face is all blurry, I think the reaper's got a hold of you!!!!!
Nice eye.  Did you even blur out your hat?
...even blur out the 'eyes eye?  Protection against identity theft?
Great report and pics Grant Congratulations on your PB It's certainly a great one for sure!!!  Keep it up Thanks for sharing Leechman
you have blurred out your gut as well.  with your paranoia for secrecy, i guess you won't share location and lure?  haha
Grant, I Think you blurred out the wrong part of your body. I'll be 62 on Monday and I have some abs I can sell ya.  Funny stuff, Dude.
Grant Way to go. How I miss your posts on here.  What happened to the internet at work, they cut everyone off?  Jose
Very nice walleye there SNAG/Grant! Possibly some big ones around seeing they spend time in Lake Ontario. Have to try fishing down there again sometime. Cheers, Erik
Way to go Snag!!  It is a good feeling isn't it?   A beauty and thanks so much for the laughs.....always enjoy your posts and blurry pictures  lol

Roy, I've gotten uglier, thus the face blur. and HAPPY BIRTHDAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! (Now your age and height are the same????)   Big brother dude! Now I'm off to the salt mines.............   Let me/us know how you do!   Thanks Carole, I was thinking of you guys at the time. (probably why it's a little blurry.....)

OMG!!!  Dat's HIDEOUS Dude!!!   Snag fishes with worms... Snag fishes with worms...... next thing yanno, you'll be eating with a baby spoon!!!   Excellent Wall-ice Bubba!!!  Glad to have you back on the board... even if you do fish with worms!  You have a stinky PM!
Classic Jim
Dude, thats a serious walleye!  I can put you on the photoshop weightloss plan if you are interested.
That sure is a beauty Snag, I love innie's  Its great when you get a surprise like that eh!!!  Gotta love it.  Joey
You're old   I like innies too!
